-- Belgian King Confirms Caretaker Role for Leterme as Coalition Talks Start
-- Kevin Costelloe
-- 2010-06-14T10:02:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/belgian-king-confirms-caretaker-role-for-leterme-as-coalition-talks-start.html

          
          
             Belgian King Albert II asked Prime
Minister Yves Leterme’s government to stay on in a caretaker
role, following yesterday’s general elections that will lead to
coalition talks expected to take at least several weeks. The
royal palace issued a statement following the king’s meeting
with Leterme today.  
          
          


  


        